<item>
            <title>[SPR-2266] Documentation for advising transactional operations (section 9.5.5) doesn&apos;t include example for tx:annotation-driven</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2266</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;The documentation on advising transaction operations (section 9.5.5) states &quot;Consider the situation where you have an instance of a class, and you would like to execute both transactional and (to keep things simple) some basic profiling advice . So how do you effect this in the context of using &amp;lt;tx:annotation-driven/&amp;gt;?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...yet the included example doesn&apos;t address tx:annotation-driven / @Transactional.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
